values: So my library is collecting zines, and letting people check them out. I don't know if this a permanent thing or just some flavor of the week, but i guess i was just wondering if anyone else out there (that means you) knows if your local library is doing the same, and if so, would you be kind enough to give me a link to it (if there is a website)?

I had a dream a few nights ago that i was the cinematographer on the movie "Hell's Angels", and we're filmming this scene with a house. Howard Hughes (who is really Philip Seymour Hoffman in my dream) comes up to me and says he wants a full shot of the house. I tell him ok. Then shortly after, people start taking the house down. Howard Hughes comes up to me and asks "Did you get that?". I say "No". Then he throws a fit.

About Log Cabin Repbulicans of Michigan Vision: We exist to promote core Republican values of liberty and equality in the State of Michigan. Mission Statement: To strength the bonds between the Michigan State Republican Party and the gay and lesbian organizations and communities by promoting core Republican values of liberty and equality. Goals: We will work to increase gay and lesbian participation within the Michigan State Republican Party through grassroots efforts statewide. Objectives: 1. To promote the growth of Log Cabin Republicans in the State of Michigan. 2. To promote the involvement of gay and lesbian organizations and communities . 3. To promote the election and appointment of fair-minded Republicans statewide. 4. Advocate for the inclusion of policies promoting equality within the Michigan State Republican Party.

It's not quite Valentine's Day yet, but here's something for VDay...

Werner Herzog As Abraham Lincoln: In an interview with Time Out London, director Werner Herzog explains that he'll be playing a part in Korine's next film, Mister Lonely, which possibly begins filming this month. His role, one has claimed, is as an Abraham Lincoln impersonator. In the same interview, when asked about his attraction to Korine's films, Herzog says, "Well his films are very, very different from mine. But I think that there is a similar quest from that man. I think that he is looking for a different grammar of images and I'm into that as well."

So i have a story to share...
Some of you may know that i just lost my car sunday... Well i get this phone call, right around the time that Kayleigh was supposed to pick me up for work, and it's Kayleigh. She says "Um you know how you were saying your car was gonna roll down the street?" Apparently I was correct...
I felt really bad, because first off I didn't want to cause damage to someone else's property due to my stupid car, and second off I didn't want my car towed away...
Kayleigh comes to pick me up, and we get over to her house and turn the corner, and her grandpa is in his chevy pushing the car up the hill. He has a big smile on his face. I could not help but laugh at the situation, nor could i stop laughing after what we did to get the car into the driveway.
It was definitely something that lightened up the situation...

According to Steve, some people don't have it that great on their 21st. I know for my 21st, i was able to crawl in my bed. So i must have had it great. Anyway, Happy Aquarius Birthdays!!!

What a dumb movie... What a Misogynistic movie. Not once did i see a penis. Only Tits and Ass. The first 45 min was like the Howard Stern show. It was the epitome of Bros on spring break. Kayleigh pointed out the fact that the music was fucking horrible and it was totally out of place, and she was right... Then the dudes start getting killed off. Sweet!!! I was so glad. I was so happy to see that two of the apes got killed. But then the main dude, doesn't get killed and he actually gets away. Then he kills the bad guy at the end. How stupid. I wanted to see everyone die!!! But NOOOOOO!!! I think the one thing that made me really mad was how exploitative the movie was to the Czech Republic. There are no street children running around the streets, willing to stone and bash people's heads in for bubble gum. This is not India. This is not Brazil. This movie had no soul. If you're gonna be exploitative, at least make a movie about slavery or the holocaust. Or both... Cool Things ---------- -Cameo by Takashi Miike... -The streets bashing these two thugs heads in for a bag of russian whore bubble gum (actually i wish the movie was really about these street kids, kinda like the movie "The Brood") -Nothing else... I was actually mad at the end when the american dude shoved the guy's face in the toilet and it wasn't covered in shit... I mean the guy was taking a dump. This movie was no Haute Tension...
